The paper deals with algorithms for data compression and string processing, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The use of Lempel-Ziv parsing and range predecessor data structures suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Information Theory (cs.IT), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), or Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper focuses on the design and analysis of algorithms, we consider cs.DS and cs.IT to be the most likely categories, followed by cs.CC, cs.DM, and cs.LG.
